The paper deals with privacy concerns related to smart meters, which are typically used in the context of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of an energy harvesting device and instantaneous power constraints also suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) aspect to the paper. Additionally, the paper presents numerical results, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or cybernetics (cs.CY).
